                    <physDesc><p>This letter is a single paged “Cablegram.” The word “Cablegram” is written in all caps,
                        underlined, and centered at the top of the page. There is a penciled in number on the left-hand
                        side of the page, halfway down, slanting upwards from left to right at a seventy-degree-angle that
                        looks like “$6.25.” It’s hard to make out the first symbol, but my best guess would be a number
                        associated with payment or cost of sending the cable. There is some embossing at the top of the
                        page in the center, but it’s difficult to make out what it could be.</p>
                    </physDesc>
